TOKA holders can submit the content data deposited with blockchain technology to various local Internet courts and arbitration committees in case of disputes. Attachment:\nSeptember 7, 2018, the Supreme People\'s Court of China announced and implemented the Provisions of the Supreme People\'s Court on Several Issues Concerning the Hearing of Cases on the Internet. The Provisions provide the adoption of an online approach to hearing cases in the Internet courts, the scope of cases to be accepted, the construction of Internet litigation platforms, the online processing of prosecution materials, the online exchange of evidence, and the electronicization of litigation and evidence materials. Among them, Article 11 states that "the parties submit electronic data, through electronic signatures, trusted timestamps, hash value verification, blockchain, and other evidence collection, fixed and tamper-proof technical means, or electronic forensic deposition platform authentication, can prove its authenticity, and the Internet Court shall confirm." Profitability Definition: the average rate of return per trade of the master in the past 30 days. The larger the value, the stronger the profitability of the individual. Profitability of Follow-Up Orders Definition: the average profitability of each trade in the last 30 days for users who follow the master. The larger the value, the better the return for the user following the master Winning Rate of Follow-up Orders Definition: the chance of following the master\'s profit. The larger the value, the higher the possibility of profitability. Popularity Index Definition: the number of followers of the master in the past 30 days. The larger the number, the more followers and the higher the popularity.
